att(con109b, pro36b).  % [undermining] conf=70 — Similarly, the critique of skirt‑length rules attacks the premise that uniforms address disciplinary drama.
att(con36, pro36c).  % [undermining] conf=70 — The criticism that an ugly uniform detracts from individuality challenges the premise that uniforms improve learning focus.
att(con109, pro36c).  % [rebuttal] conf=90 — Con109 says uniforms are unlikely to solve academic issues, directly contradicting pro36c’s claim that uniforms increase focus on learning.
att(con109b, pro36c).  % [rebuttal] conf=90 — Con109b similarly argues that uniform‑related decrees won’t solve discipline/academic problems, opposing pro36c’s positive effect on learning.
